quran[24]{c,v,t}:
  38,65,"Say, ˹O Prophet,˺ “I am only a warner. And there is no god ˹worthy of worship˺ except God—the One, the Supreme"
  38,66,"˹He is the˺ Lord of the heavens and the earth and everything in between—the Almighty, Most Forgiving.”"
  38,67,"Say, “This ˹Quran˺ is momentous news"
  38,68,from which you ˹pagans˺ are turning away.”
  38,69,"˹And say,˺ “I had no knowledge of the highest assembly ˹in heaven˺ when they differed ˹concerning Adam˺"
  38,70,What is revealed to me is that I am only sent with a clear warning.”
  38,71,"˹Remember, O Prophet˺ when your Lord said to the angels, “I am going to create a human being from clay"
  38,72,"So when I have fashioned him and had a spirit of My Own ˹creation˺ breathed into him, fall down in prostration to him.”"
  38,73,So the angels prostrated all together—
  38,74,"but not Iblîs, who acted arrogantly, becoming unfaithful"
  38,75,"God asked, “O Iblîs! What prevented you from prostrating to what I created with My Own Hands? Did you ˹just˺ become proud? Or have you always been arrogant?”"
  38,76,"He replied, “I am better than he is: You created me from fire and him from clay.”"
  38,77,"God commanded, “Then get out of Paradise, for you are truly cursed"
  38,78,And surely upon you is My condemnation until the Day of Judgment.”
  38,79,"Satan appealed, “My Lord! Then delay my end until the Day of their resurrection.”"
  38,80,"God said, “You will be delayed"
  38,81,until the appointed Day.”
  38,82,"Satan said, “By Your Glory! I will certainly mislead them all"
  38,83,except Your chosen servants among them.”
  38,84,"God concluded, “The truth is—and I ˹only˺ say the truth—"
  38,85,"I will surely fill up Hell with you and whoever follows you from among them, all together.”"
  38,86,"Say, ˹O Prophet,˺ “I do not ask you for any reward for this ˹Quran˺, nor do I pretend to be someone I am not"
  38,87,It is only a reminder to the whole world
  38,88,And you will certainly know its truth before long.”